443
00:14:36,963 --> 00:14:39,226
And that's when he moved up,
got more stable hours.

444
00:14:39,269 --> 00:14:40,967
Mm.

445
00:14:41,010 --> 00:14:44,144
I mean,
I always loved him --

446
00:14:44,187 --> 00:14:46,929
don't get me wrong --
even when he wasn't around.

447
00:14:46,973 --> 00:14:50,063
I have a lot of
great memories, you know?

448
00:14:50,106 --> 00:14:51,629
Of course.

449
00:14:51,673 --> 00:14:54,458
You know, you and Wesley are
going to be awesome parents.

450
00:14:54,502 --> 00:14:56,591
I know.

451
00:14:56,634 --> 00:14:58,201
It's just...

452
00:14:58,245 --> 00:15:00,247
We both get so wrapped up
in our cases,

453
00:15:00,290 --> 00:15:03,380
we barely make timeto have dinner together.

454
00:15:03,424 --> 00:15:05,121
How are we supposed tomake time for a kid?

455
00:15:05,165 --> 00:15:08,298
Wesley is loaded.
You get yourself a nanny.

456
00:15:08,342 --> 00:15:09,734
Or three.

457
00:15:09,778 --> 00:15:11,040
So a stranger
can raise my child?

458
00:15:11,084 --> 00:15:12,302
I mean,
it won't be a stranger

459
00:15:12,346 --> 00:15:14,870
